OL,6,FForeign Secretary Lord Cameron
OL,7,Fcondemned Mr Williams's move as "very
OL,8,Ffoolish". The Cabinet minister told
OL,9,FBBC Breakfast that Mr Williams is
OL,10,Falready standing as a Conservative
OL,11,Fcandidate and "I don't think we can
OL,12,Fchange that", adding Mr Williams "will
OL,13,Fhave to face the consequences" of the
OL,14,FGambling Commission probe.
OL,16,FJonathan Ashworth, Labour's Shadow
OL,17,FPaymaster General described the
OL,18,Fallegations as "utterly extraordinary".
